    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Terraced pavilions, one of the principal forms of buildings in East Asian gardens. Such buildings are generally constructed beside water, and thus are called “water pavilions.”</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
